deck: Anteiku is a small cafe in the 20th ward.
description:
Anteiku (あんていく) is a small cafe shop in the peaceful 20th ward. The shop serves both humans and ghouls. It also acts as the ghoul headquarters for the area. Since the ghouls in the area do not actively hunt humans, Anteiku also acts as a procurement and storage facility for those ghouls who cannot hunt for themselves. Anteiku itself does not hunt humans, rather collects bodies of people that commit suicide.

Anteiku also maintains hunting grounds for the ghouls in the area. It is the primary ghoul organization in the area and also acts as a refuge in times of need.

Anteiku also connects to a series of tunnels deep below the city that were once used by Ghouls to move around but has been abandoned since.

deck: The original place where Johnny Thunder and his pink Thunderbolt were mystically linked.
description:
Badhnesia (or Badhnisia, Badnhesia or Bahdnesia) is was a country in the original earth 2 where Johnny Thunder was tied to the magic Thunderbolt. Because of several retellings is unclear where is exactly, vary from a pacific island, a middle Europe country or an middle east Asia nation.

In the composed earth post crisis Badhnesia reappered as a wasted land because of the absence of the magic Thunderbolt with the adopted daughter of Johnny Thunder, Kiku, as the last badhnesian.

In Crisis Times Five, this was retconned with several people living in the middle-east like country, inspired in the Arabian Nights tales. The wise men from Badhnesia, a group of expert scientifics, adviced Captain Marvel how to deal with the impending attack from the fifth dimension.
